The paper deals with software vulnerabilities and their mapping to software weaknesses, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The validation of textual information retrieval techniques is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of regular expression searches and keyword-based searches suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL). The topic of software vulnerabilities also relates to computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for information retrieval could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
